      "content": "A hiring committee or academic board would almost certainly judge Text A as more \"capable\" because it adheres to the established norms of formal, educated discourse. Text A uses specialized vocabulary and complex syntax, which are often mistakenly equated with intellectual rigor in those gatekeeping environments. Text B, while perfectly clear, uses vernacular features that these institutions often misinterpret as a lack of formal education or cognitive depth. This reflects a systemic bias where adherence to a dominant dialect is wrongly conflated with actual intelligence.",
