      "content": "The perceived link between dialect and cognitive testing is often a reflection of cultural biases embedded within those very tests, not an objective measure of raw intelligence. While academic fields demand a certain register for professional communication, this requirement is a tool of social gatekeeping, not a pure measure of intellect. To suggest that using a non-standard dialect equates to a deficit in abstract reasoning ignores the vast capacity for complex thought present in all linguistic communities. Lowering the bar for \"fairness\" is often a political move, but maintaining the standard is frequently a mechanism for maintaining existing hierarchies.",
